{"questionId":"35032174","questionHtml":"<p>Find the values of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"p\">\n  <mi>p</mi>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"q\">\n  <mi>q</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"p = 1\">\n  <mi>p</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"q =&nbsp; - 4\">\n  <mi>q</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong>Note:</strong> If <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"p\">\n  <mi>p</mi>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"q\">\n  <mi>q</mi>\n</math></span> are both incorrect then award <em><strong>M1A0</strong> </em>for an attempt&nbsp;to solve simultaneous equations.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"35032174","referenceCode":"SPM.2.SL.TZ0.5a.ii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the values of p and q .","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Modelling skills"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}